          "cookies": [],
          "content": {
            "size": 23815,
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "text": "{\"templates\":[{\"id\":\"tmpl-catalog-sample-request\",\"name\":\"Catalog & Sample Request\",\"description\":\"Logs requests for catalogs, brochures, price lists, and physical samples, then tracks them through to dispatch.\",\"mode\":\"periodic\",\"cron_interval\":\"*/20 * * * *\",\"prompt\":\"'You are a structured data extraction assistant.\\n\\nYour job is to process a batch of WhatsApp messages.\\n\\nBefore extracting data, determine whether each message is relevant according to the user-provided guidance.\\n\\nIMPORTANT:\\n- The guidance may define what messages should be extracted.\\n- Only create output records for messages that satisfy the guidance.\\n- Ignore messages that do not satisfy the guidance.\\n- If the guidance does not specify any filtering criteria, process all messages.\\n\\nFor matching messages:\\n- Extract the requested fields.\\n- Preserve original message content verbatim.\\n- If a field cannot be determined, leave it empty.'\",\"config\":\"{\\\"tools\\\": [], \\\"waConfigId\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"groups\\\": [], \\\"columns\\\": [{\\\"name\\\": \\\"Request ID\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Request ID in format CAT-{YEAR}-{SEQUENCE:05d} (e.g., CAT-2026-00001). Generate from current year and an incrementing 5-digit sequence.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Request Type\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"One of: Catalog, Sample, Brochure, Price List. 'Catalog' for product catalogue/booklet, 'Sample' for physical product samples, 'Brochure' for company/flyer brochures, 'Price List' for rate sheets.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Product / Category\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Product name or category the customer is interested in (e.g., 'TMT Bars', 'Electrical switches'). For Catalog/Price List requests where no specific product is mentioned, capture the general category or leave empty.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Quantity\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Number of samples or copies requested. Leave empty if not specified.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Delivery Address\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Full delivery address provided by the customer. If the customer says 'same address as last time' or 'you already have it', note that and leave the field empty — the team will look it up.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Status\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Set to 'New' for every new request. Tracked by the team: New → Sent → Delivered\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Dispatched Date\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Date the materials were dispatched in DD-Mon-YYYY format — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Courier / Tracking No.\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Courier name and tracking/AWB number — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Assigned To\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Team member responsible for fulfilling this request — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Notes\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Any additional context — urgency, special instructions, customer's timeline, follow-up preferences. Added by the LLM during extraction, enriched by the team later.\\\"}], \\\"search_tags\\\": [], \\\"guidance\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"webhook_guidance\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"spreadsheet_id\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"spreadsheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"sheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"actions\\\": [], \\\"example_guidance\\\": {\\\"guidance\\\": \\\"For each message, detect catalog, sample, brochure, and price list requests. Critical rules:\\n1. Request ID must use format CAT-{year}-{5-digit sequence starting from 00001}. Example: CAT-2026-00001.\\n2. Request Type: Catalog = 'send your catalogue', 'product book'; Sample = 'can I get a sample of X', 'send me a piece'; Brochure = 'share brochure', 'company profile'; Price List = 'send rate list', 'price sheet'.\\n3. If the customer asks for a price list ONLY (no physical send needed), still capture it — the fulfilment may be digital (WhatsApp/email) but tracking it here keeps all requests in one place.\\n4. This is DISTINCT from Enquiry & Quotation — do NOT capture buying-intent enquiries here. Only capture explicit requests to send/receive materials. If a customer says 'what's the price of X' without asking for a price list to be sent, that belongs in the Enquiry & Quotation tracker, NOT here.\\n5. Set Status to 'New' for every new request.\\n6. Do NOT guess or generate: Dispatched Date, Courier / Tracking No., Assigned To — always leave them empty. The team fills them after dispatch.\\n7. Delivery Address is critical for physical fulfilment. Extract it verbatim. If the address is incomplete, note what's missing in Notes.\\n8. In Notes, capture: whether the request is urgent, preferred delivery method mentioned, if the customer is a repeat requester, and any special handling instructions.\\\"}}\",\"custom_workflow_type\":\"GroupsToSheetsWorkflow\",\"agentCount\":0},{\"id\":\"tmpl-categorise-messages\",\"name\":\"Categorise Messages\",\"description\":\"Create custom categories to organize WhatsApp conversations across orders, payments, dispatch, support, inventory, and internal operations.\",\"mode\":\"periodic\",\"cron_interval\":\"*/20 * * * *\",\"prompt\":\"You are a message categorisation agent. Read each message and assign it to one or more categories from the configured list. Return the message content along with its category labels.\",\"config\":\"{}\",\"custom_workflow_type\":\"GroupsToSheetsWorkflow\",\"agentCount\":0},{\"id\":\"tmpl-collect-leads\",\"name\":\"Collect New Leads\",\"description\":\"Capture and organize potential customer enquiries from WhatsApp groups automatically. Identify interested buyers, track follow-ups, and streamline lead conversion workflows.\",\"mode\":\"periodic\",\"cron_interval\":\"*/20 * * * *\",\"prompt\":\"You are a lead collection agent. Identify potential customer enquiries from messages. Extract name, phone, product interest, and any explicit buying signals. Flag high-intent leads.\",\"config\":\"{}\",\"custom_workflow_type\":\"GroupsToSheetsWorkflow\",\"agentCount\":0},{\"id\":\"tmpl-complaint-tracker\",\"name\":\"Complaint Tracker\",\"description\":\"Surfaces customer dissatisfaction from group chat — defects, delays, billing errors, damaged goods, service issues.\",\"mode\":\"periodic\",\"cron_interval\":\"*/20 * * * *\",\"prompt\":\"'You are a structured data extraction assistant.\\n\\nYour job is to process a batch of WhatsApp messages.\\n\\nBefore extracting data, determine whether each message is relevant according to the user-provided guidance.\\n\\nIMPORTANT:\\n- The guidance may define what messages should be extracted.\\n- Only create output records for messages that satisfy the guidance.\\n- Ignore messages that do not satisfy the guidance.\\n- If the guidance does not specify any filtering criteria, process all messages.\\n\\nFor matching messages:\\n- Extract the requested fields.\\n- Preserve original message content verbatim.\\n- If a field cannot be determined, leave it empty.'\",\"config\":\"{\\\"tools\\\": [], \\\"waConfigId\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"groups\\\": [], \\\"columns\\\": [{\\\"name\\\": \\\"Complaint ID\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Complaint ID in format CMP-{YEAR}-{SEQUENCE:05d} (e.g., CMP-2026-00001). Generate from current year and an incrementing 5-digit sequence.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Complaint Category\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"One of: Defect, Delay, Billing, Damaged, Service, Other. Classify based on the customer's grievance.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Severity\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"One of: Low, Medium, High, Critical. Assess based on tone (anger/urgency), financial impact mentioned, and whether the customer threatens escalation. When in doubt, default to   Medium.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Product/Order Ref\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Product name, order number, or invoice reference mentioned. Leave empty if none.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Complaint Summary\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Concise summary of the complaint — what went wrong, when it happened, what the customer expects. Include key details like dates, amounts, and specific grievances.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Status\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Set to 'Open' for every new complaint. Tracked by the team: Open → In Progress → Resolved → Closed\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Assigned To\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Team member handling this complaint — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Resolution Notes\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"How the complaint was resolved — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Resolved Date\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Date the complaint was resolved in DD-Mon-YYYY format — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}], \\\"search_tags\\\": [], \\\"guidance\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"webhook_guidance\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"spreadsheet_id\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"spreadsheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"sheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"actions\\\": [], \\\"example_guidance\\\": {\\\"guidance\\\": \\\"For each message, detect customer complaints and grievances. Critical rules:\\n1. Complaint ID must use format CMP-{year}-{5-digit sequence starting from 00001}. Example: CMP-2026-00001.\\n2. Category must be exactly one of: Defect (product quality/manufacturing issues), Delay (late delivery/shipment), Billing (wrong charges/invoice errors), Damaged (goods arrived damaged), Service (rude staff/poor support), Other (anything not fitting above).\\n3. Severity: Low (minor issue, polite tone), Medium (clear frustration, moderate impact), High (anger, significant financial loss, demand for urgent action), Critical (legal threats, regulatory complaints, public escalation risk).\\n4. If the message is a casual complaint/vent with no request for action, still capture it — the team decides whether to act.\\n5. If multiple messages form a single complaint thread, capture ONE row summarising the whole thread, not one per message.\\n6. Set Status to 'Open' for every new complaint.\\n7. Do NOT guess or generate: Assigned To, Resolution Notes, Resolved Date — always leave them empty. The team fills them later.\\n8. In Complaint Summary, capture: what happened, when, the customer's stated expectation or demand, and any reference numbers/names mentioned.\\\"}}\",\"custom_workflow_type\":\"GroupsToSheetsWorkflow\",\"agentCount\":0},{\"id\":\"tmpl-dispatch-tracker\",\"name\":\"Dispatch Tracker\",\"description\":\"Triages dispatch and logistics queries (ETA, tracking, not received, address change) so they dont get buried in busy groups.\",\"mode\":\"periodic\",\"cron_interval\":\"*/20 * * * *\",\"prompt\":\"'You are a structured data extraction assistant.\\n\\nYour job is to process a batch of WhatsApp messages.\\n\\nBefore extracting data, determine whether each message is relevant according to the user-provided guidance.\\n\\nIMPORTANT:\\n- The guidance may define what messages should be extracted.\\n- Only create output records for messages that satisfy the guidance.\\n- Ignore messages that do not satisfy the guidance.\\n- If the guidance does not specify any filtering criteria, process all messages.\\n\\nFor matching messages:\\n- Extract the requested fields.\\n- Preserve original message content verbatim.\\n- If a field cannot be determined, leave it empty.'\",\"config\":\"{\\\"tools\\\": [], \\\"waConfigId\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"groups\\\": [], \\\"columns\\\": [{\\\"name\\\": \\\"Enquiry ID\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Enquiry ID in format ENQ-{YEAR}-{SEQUENCE:05d} (e.g., ENQ-2026-00001). Generate from current year and an incrementing 5-digit sequence.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Query Type\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"One of: ETA, Tracking, Not received, Address change. Classify based on the customer's question.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Order/Invoice Ref\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Order number, invoice number, or any reference ID mentioned in the message. Leave empty if none.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Dispatch Status\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Set to 'Pending' for every new enquiry — the team updates this later.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Courier/Transporter\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Courier or transporter name if mentioned (e.g., BlueDart, DTDC, Delhivery). Leave empty if unknown.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"LR / Docket / AWB No.\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"LR number, docket number, or AWB number if provided. Leave empty if not mentioned.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Expected Delivery\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Expected delivery date in DD-Mon-YYYY format (e.g., 20-Jun-2026). Extract from message if mentioned, otherwise leave empty.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Resolution Notes\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Summary of what was communicated to the customer — added later by the team.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Status\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Tracked by the team: Pending → Dispatched → In Transit → Delivered → Issue\\\"}], \\\"search_tags\\\": [], \\\"guidance\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"webhook_guidance\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"spreadsheet_id\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"spreadsheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"sheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"actions\\\": [], \\\"example_guidance\\\": {\\\"guidance\\\": \\\"For each message, detect dispatch/logistics queries. Critical rules:\\n1. Enquiry ID must use format ENQ-{year}-{5-digit sequence starting from 00001}. Example: ENQ-2026-04819.\\n2. Query Type must be exactly one of: ETA (ship/delivery time questions), Tracking (LR/docket/AWB/courier status), Not received (order hasn't arrived), Address change (customer wants to update delivery address).\\n3. If no logistics query is detected, do NOT create a row — skip the message.\\n4. Set Dispatch Status to 'Pending' and Status to 'Pending' for every new enquiry.\\n5. Do NOT guess Order/Invoice Ref, Courier/Transporter, LR/Docket/AWB, or Expected Delivery — only extract what is explicitly mentioned.\\n6. Leave Resolution Notes empty — the team fills it later.\\\", \\\"webhook_guidance\\\": \\\"\\\"}}\",\"custom_workflow_type\":\"GroupsToSheetsWorkflow\",\"agentCount\":0},{\"id\":\"tmpl-enquiry-quotation\",\"name\":\"Enquiry & Quotation\",\"description\":\"Captures buying-intent enquiries and explicit quote/price-list requests, carrying them through one lifecycle that ends in a quote.\",\"mode\":\"periodic\",\"cron_interval\":\"*/20 * * * *\",\"prompt\":\"'You are a structured data extraction assistant.\\n\\nYour job is to process a batch of WhatsApp messages.\\n\\nBefore extracting data, determine whether each message is relevant according to the user-provided guidance.\\n\\nIMPORTANT:\\n- The guidance may define what messages should be extracted.\\n- Only create output records for messages that satisfy the guidance.\\n- Ignore messages that do not satisfy the guidance.\\n- If the guidance does not specify any filtering criteria, process all messages.\\n\\nFor matching messages:\\n- Extract the requested fields.\\n- Preserve original message content verbatim.\\n- If a field cannot be determined, leave it empty.'\",\"config\":\"{\\\"tools\\\": [], \\\"waConfigId\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"groups\\\": [], \\\"columns\\\": [{\\\"name\\\": \\\"Enquiry ID\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Enquiry ID in format ENQ-{YEAR}-{SEQUENCE:05d} (e.g., ENQ-2026-00001). Generate from current year and an incrementing 5-digit sequence.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Request Type\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"One of: Enquiry, Quote, Price List. 'Enquiry' for buying-intent/availability questions, 'Quote' for explicit price requests for specific items, 'Price List' for general   price-list/catalogue requests.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Product/Item\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Product or item name mentioned in the message. If multiple items, list the primary one here and note others in Summary.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Quantity\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Quantity requested, if explicitly mentioned. Leave empty if not specified.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Summary\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Brief summary of the enquiry — key details, any additional items, special requirements mentioned by the customer.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Status\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Set to 'New' for every new enquiry. Tracked by the team: New → In Progress → Quoted → Won / Lost\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Quoted Price\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Final quoted price — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Quote Sent Date\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Date the quote was sent to customer — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Last Status Update\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Timestamp of last status change — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Status Sent to Customer?\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Yes/No — whether status was communicated to the customer. Added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Assigned To\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Team member handling this enquiry — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Next Action\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Next step for the team — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}], \\\"search_tags\\\": [], \\\"guidance\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"webhook_guidance\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"spreadsheet_id\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"spreadsheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"sheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"actions\\\": [], \\\"example_guidance\\\": {\\\"guidance\\\": \\\"For each message, detect buying-intent enquiries and quote/price requests. Critical rules:\\n1. Enquiry ID must use format ENQ-{year}-{5-digit sequence starting from 00001}. Example: ENQ-2026-04819.\\n2. Request Type must be exactly one of: Enquiry (availability, 'do you have X', 'can you supply'), Quote (explicit price request for specific items), Price List (general catalogue/price-list request, 'send me your rates').\\n3. If the message is a casual conversation, greeting, thank-you, or non-buying-intent — do NOT create a row. Skip it.\\n4. Set Status to 'New' for every new enquiry.\\n5. Do NOT guess or generate: Quoted Price, Quote Sent Date, Last Status Update, Status Sent to Customer?, Assigned To, Next Action — always leave them empty. The team fills them later.\\n6. If the customer asks about multiple items, capture the primary one in Product/Item and list all items in Summary.\\\", \\\"webhook_guidance\\\": \\\"\\\"}}\",\"custom_workflow_type\":\"GroupsToSheetsWorkflow\",\"agentCount\":0},{\"id\":\"tmpl-groups-to-sheets\",\"name\":\"Groups to Sheets\",\"description\":\"Periodically scans WhatsApp group messages via OpenSearch, extracts structured enquiry details (sender name, phone number, message content, timestamp), and writes them to a configured Google Sheet.\",\"mode\":\"periodic\",\"cron_interval\":\"*/20 * * * *\",\"prompt\":\"'You are a structured data extraction assistant.\\n\\nYour job is to process a batch of WhatsApp messages.\\n\\nBefore extracting data, determine whether each message is relevant according to the user-provided guidance.\\n\\nIMPORTANT:\\n- The guidance may define what messages should be extracted.\\n- Only create output records for messages that satisfy the guidance.\\n- Ignore messages that do not satisfy the guidance.\\n- If the guidance does not specify any filtering criteria, process all messages.\\n\\nFor matching messages:\\n- Extract the requested fields.\\n- Preserve original message content verbatim.\\n- If a field cannot be determined, leave it empty.'\",\"config\":\"{   \\\"tools\\\": [],   \\\"waConfigId\\\": \\\"\\\",   \\\"columns\\\": [     {       \\\"name\\\": \\\"group_name\\\",       \\\"description\\\": \\\"Name of the WhatsApp group the message was sent to\\\"     },     {       \\\"name\\\": \\\"sender\\\",       \\\"description\\\": \\\"Name of the sender who sent the message\\\"     },     { \\\"name\\\": \\\"phone_number\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Phone number of the sender\\\" },     {       \\\"name\\\": \\\"message\\\",       \\\"description\\\": \\\"Actual message content sent by the sender\\\"     },     {       \\\"name\\\": \\\"timestamp\\\",       \\\"description\\\": \\\"Timestamp of when the message was sent\\\"     }   ],   \\\"search_tags\\\": [],   \\\"guidance\\\": \\\"\\\",   \\\"webhook_guidance\\\": \\\"\\\",   \\\"example_guidance\\\": {     \\\"guidance\\\": \\\"\\\",     \\\"webhook_guidance\\\": \\\"\\\"   },   \\\"spreadsheet_id\\\": \\\"\\\",   \\\"spreadsheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\",   \\\"sheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\",   \\\"groups\\\": [],   \\\"actions\\\": [] }\",\"custom_workflow_type\":\"GroupsToSheetsWorkflow\",\"agentCount\":1},{\"id\":\"tmpl-payment-outstanding\",\"name\":\"Payment & Outstanding\",\"description\":\"Tracks money-related chatter — payment confirmations, promises, and balance queries — in one place.\",\"mode\":\"periodic\",\"cron_interval\":\"*/20 * * * *\",\"prompt\":\"'You are a structured data extraction assistant.\\n\\nYour job is to process a batch of WhatsApp messages.\\n\\nBefore extracting data, determine whether each message is relevant according to the user-provided guidance.\\n\\nIMPORTANT:\\n- The guidance may define what messages should be extracted.\\n- Only create output records for messages that satisfy the guidance.\\n- Ignore messages that do not satisfy the guidance.\\n- If the guidance does not specify any filtering criteria, process all messages.\\n\\nFor matching messages:\\n- Extract the requested fields.\\n- Preserve original message content verbatim.\\n- If a field cannot be determined, leave it empty.'\",\"config\":\"{\\\"tools\\\": [], \\\"waConfigId\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"groups\\\": [], \\\"columns\\\": [{\\\"name\\\": \\\"Payment ID\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Payment ID in format PAY-{YEAR}-{SEQUENCE:05d} (e.g., PAY-2026-00001). Generate from current year and an incrementing 5-digit sequence.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Payment Type\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"One of: Confirmation, Promise, Query. 'Confirmation' for payments made with UTR/reference, 'Promise' for commitments to pay by a future date, 'Query' for balance/outstanding/due-amount questions.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Amount\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Amount mentioned in the message (numeric, no currency symbol). Leave empty if no amount is specified.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Payment Mode\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"One of: UPI, NEFT, Cheque, Cash. Extract from message if mentioned. Leave empty if unknown.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Reference / UTR No.\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"UTR number, cheque number, or any payment reference provided. Leave empty if none.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Invoice/Order Ref\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Invoice number or order reference the payment is against. Leave empty if not mentioned.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Promised Date\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Date the customer committed to pay, in DD-Mon-YYYY format (e.g., 25-Jun-2026). Only fill for Payment Type = Promise. Leave empty for Confirmations and Queries.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Status\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"For Confirmations: set to 'Reported'. For Promises: set to 'Pending'. For Queries: set to 'Reported'. Tracked by the team: Reported → Verified → Reconciled; Pending is for unverified promises.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Verified By\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Team member who verified the payment — added later by the team. Always leave empty during extraction.\\\"}, {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Notes\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Any additional context — customer remarks, partial-payment details, payment-plan discussions, follow-up required. Added by the LLM during extraction, enriched by the team later.\\\"}], \\\"search_tags\\\": [], \\\"guidance\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"webhook_guidance\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"spreadsheet_id\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"spreadsheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"sheet_name\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"actions\\\": [], \\\"example_guidance\\\": {\\\"guidance\\\": \\\"For each message, detect payment-related chatter. Critical rules:\\n1. Payment ID must use format PAY-{year}-{5-digit sequence starting from 00001}. Example: PAY-2026-00001.\\n2. Payment Type: Confirmation = 'paid X, UTR Y', 'transferred Z', 'payment done'; Promise = 'will pay by Friday', 'clearing next week', 'I'll settle by month end'; Query = 'what's my due', 'how much outstanding', 'send statement', 'balance kitna hai'.\\n3. If the message is general money chat with no actionable payment event (e.g., 'ok thanks for the bill'), do NOT create a row.\\n4. For Promises: ALWAYS capture the Promised Date. If the customer says 'by Friday' and today is Monday, resolve to the actual date. If they say 'next week' without a day, leave Promised Date empty but note the ambiguity in Notes.\\n5. Status defaults: Confirmation → 'Reported', Promise → 'Pending', Query → 'Reported'.\\n6. Do NOT guess or generate: Verified By — always leave empty. The team fills it after bank verification.\\n7. The high-value output is the Promise list — Promises with dates create a follow-up queue. Capture every promise accurately and include the commitment date.\\n8. In Notes, capture: partial payment mentions, 'remaining balance' context, disputes, or any condition the customer attached to the payment ('will pay after delivery', 'holding until quality check').\\\", \\\"webhook_guidance\\\": \\\"\\\"}}\",\"custom_workflow_type\":\"GroupsToSheetsWorkflow\",\"agentCount\":0}]}"
          },
